====&gt; since you wanting input,  i don't know if you are wanting input on
RCOG or one of the courses of treatment.

as far as RCOG,  a web research will turn up a lot and you should be
able to get ahold of people who may have used their services as a
reference.

as to selecting a course of treatment,  there is an order in the course
of treatments.

given your stats,  it goes surgery, radiation and finally hormone
therapy.

there are variables that come into play on each of the options that can
alter the final choice of treatment.

for example - on surgery,  that depends on your general health and can
you stand a surgery?   another point to consider is that you could be
healthy enough right now to have surgery, but something come up like a
heart condition, etc, etc that would remove that option from the table
and radiation would be the choice of treatment then.

it's really a case by case decision, with the final choice being that of
the individual as to what they feel is best for them.

just remember that each person who is offering a choice of treatment is
a salesman.  they are going to tell you that their method is the best.

an example, would be like a surgeon at a hospital that has a million
dollar robotic machine sitting idle, isn't going to tell to have
radiation.     a doctor at a radiology clinic isn't going to tell you to
go have surgery.

well, you get the drift.

all the best,

