Les,

I live in Atlanta and I visited this facility. All in all, I was very
impressed. However, I put more faith in the doctor than the
organization. I found that several of the most experienced doctors had
had a falling out with the main man, Dr. Critz and had left. The more
research I did, the more I liked what I heard about the number two guy
who had left. His name is Dr. Hamilton Williams. He now has his own
practice, doing almost the exact techniques as RCOG. He has made some
substantial improvements over RCOG. I chose to go with him and I've
been extremely happy with my outcome so far.

If you want to really learn about RCOG, you could inquire at a
newsgroup at http://health.groups.yahoo.com/group/RCOGgroup/messages/1695?viscount... .

If you want to know more about Dr. Williams, you can go to
http://www.radoncatlanta.com/Williams.htm .

